ctual conditions in Ire\nland's fight for freedom. Mrs;\nMacSwiney is 23 years old. This\nis the first picture of her without\nhat\nMARKETS STILL\nSHOW DEPRESSION\nContinued\nAdverse Financial\nNews Causes a General\nBusiness Depression.\nGrains Yield,\nNEW FINANCE CORPORATION\nFunctioning Soon of New Body Should\nProve of Great Benefit to .Manu\nfacturinR and Agricultural\nInterests of Nation.\nMinneapolis, Minn., December 27th\n\u2014The Quinn-Shepardson Company of\nthis city has submitted the following\nreport for market conditions during:\nthe week which has just closed:\nDuring the fore part of the week\nextreme weakness of stocks occasioned\nby continual adverse financial news\ncaught our grain markets in a waiting\nmood for new developments, so that\nthe general business depression was\nagain brought to the front and grains\nwere forced to yield somewhat. There\nwas nevertheless evidence of a stub\nborn disposition toward declines, re\nsulting, no doubt, from reports show\ning still no great selling anxiety on\nthe part of producers.\nIt is estimated that about i0\nmillion bushels of North Ameri\ncan Wheat has been sold of ex\nport during the past three weeks.\nAt the rate of ten middion bush\nels weekly it might be expected\nsufficiency of U. S. supplies of hard\nmilling wheat.\nCorn finally has met a strong de\nmand and receipts everywhere are\nreadily absorbed. Considering the\nsize of the crop the movement is quite\ndisappointing. Apparently sales from\nfirst hands are forced through necess\nity. Wherever possible growers are\nreported to be holding for a minimum\nof 50c per bushel.\nOats are still without export stimu\nlus of any other noticeable demand\nexcept elevator interests where even\nthe carrying charge is unattractive.\nValues are maintained on very light\nreceipts and there is some investment\nbuying attracted by the low price and\nprobability of export demand.\nOutside the grain markets the com\nmodity trend continues uneasv and\ndrifting downward. Industrial con\nditions are confusing. Reductions\nhave been made drastic, however, that\nthere is now a very wide spread belief\nthat the cheaper commodities and\ngrains more than discount stringent\ncredits and the rather dubious business\nconditions prevailing and that from\nnow on any decided trend should be in\nthe way of an upward reaction.\nOf constructive news the launching\nlast week of the Federal Finance Cor\nporation under an impetus that pre\nsages a successful future is consid\nered the most important and practical\nof the many cures recommended. No\nthing permanent in the way of Federal\ncontrol appears contemplated but the\nfunctioning soon of the corporation\nshould prove of great benefit particu\nlarly to the manufacturing and agri\nculture industries in opening an imme\ndiate outlet for surplus supplies, re\nlieving strained credits and paving the\npresent clogged trade channels for the\nlater resumption of normal business\nunder private enterprise and the broad\neconomic law of supply and demand.\nOverseas demand for our surplus is\nmost urgent, the problem is one of\nfinance on a scale difficult under ex\nisting conditions for individuals.\nSPECIAL ELECTION TO\nCHOOSE STATE SENATOR\nHelena, Dec. 30.\u2014Upon receiving\nthe resignation of State Senator A. D.\nStrouf of Judith Basin county, Gover\nnor S. V. Stewart Monday issued a\nproclamation calling for a special elec\ntion to select his successor. Mr.\nStrouf is a resident of Stanford.\nChamberlain 's Cough Remedy.\nNow is the time to lay in a supply of\nChamberlain's Cough Remedy. It is\nalmost sure to be needed before the\nu inter is over. ou will look a good\nwhile before you find a better remedy\nfor coughs, colds, croup and whoop\ning cough or one that is more pleasant\nto take. It meets with favor every\nwhere. Buy it now and be prepared.\nMrs. Bullock Recommends Chamber\nI i\n25 M\nToilet\nPreparations\nHall Drug Co.\nKBHSMZKEM255SKSMEMEfS3MESE5IS","height":"21864","width":"16800"}}
